title: Don't Let Me Go
body:
song: Dont Let Me Go \ Harry Styles

This one sucks. sorry. I suck. sorry :(

Harry was sulking on his bed made for two. It was half empty, just like his heart. It had only been a month. 

“So why are you here if its not what you want?” 

“I won’t be.”

His head turns to the frame on his nightstand near the window carrying raindrops. It was a freeze frame from them in Jamaica. They were holding onto each other in the water. He remembers here shouting in between giggles asking him not to let her go in the water. 

“Harry! Please don’t let me go,” she giggled.

Sniffles the loudest sound in his master bedroom. He laid onto his back again. Covering his eyes with his ring clad hands. A choked sob came out of his mouth. Tears eventually following in pursuit. They slowly fell down the sides of his face. “Fuck.” 

She had been on his mind since she had walked out of the front door. They argued about how their careers were in the way, especially her current one according to Harry. He complained to her about how she didn’t support him enough because of all her work for her films. Now he regrets being such an idiot about it all. Y/N sacrificed so much to go and see as many of his shows that she could. She even took time off for Jamaica for god sakes. He was the selfish one. Not her.

If anything he could have supported her a lot more, instead of complaining. “M’such a fucking prick,” Harry yelled at himself. The sound of the rain and him exhausted after crying helped him fall into a much needed rest. The next day he was attending an event he sure wasn’t going to miss.

The morning sun loomed on him hours later. He forgot to close the curtains the night before so he was rudely awoken. He groaned stretching out his limbs in all directions. His legs lead him to the window, outside there was a wet sidewalk and cloudy skies. 

The day went by rather slowly. Harry paced around in anticipation awaiting for his stylist to come and assist him in looking his best for tonight’s carpet. 

“Lou thank god, you’re finally here,” Harry sighed. She laughed stepping in his house taking her boots off at the door. “Its gonna come down hard later. Sure you wanna go?” Harry nodded frantically sitting in his styling chair. “Cant miss this Lou. Really have to be there. Not an option.” She smiled and started to pull out the products for his hair. 

Hours. It felt like hours. Years maybe. “Bub stop moving around in ya seat. Ill mess up this mop of yours,” Harry apologized and promised to sit still. She was done before he knew it. Hopping into his suit patting it down gently, wanting to look his best. 

“Go get em,” Harry kissed Lou’s cheek and headed out to the car. The clouds were coming back in around them. The ride there was quick. Harry thanked himself for buying a house so close to where all the events in Hollywood happen. 

As soon as he stepped out the town car flashes bombarded him. So did everyones questions. He looked around not spotting her. She’s here somewhere, this is here movie. The really big one that was a really big deal. The one he should’ve supported more from the start. After taking some pictures he was escorted to his spot in the theater. Familiar faces everywhere. He made sure to politely say hello to all of his acquaintances. 

From his seat his eyes widened. Her beautiful laugh he could never forget. His eyes scanning the crowd. There she was near the front by the screen. In the front row with her costars. Instead of next to him like originally planned. Her fair half up, half down in curls. Her beautiful feathery big black dress. The one she had excitedly shown him the designs of a while back.

He felt a bit of tears coming on again, good thing the lights started to dim for the start of the film. 

The whole time Harry kept his composure, until towards the ending of course. Y/N’s performance was so emotional and pure. Harry cried. He cried at her talent, and how proud he was of his girl. She was such a hard worker and deserved to be appreciated. She deserved to be supported with all of him. Once the movie came to an end everyone applauded and stood on there feet. The actors and actresses facing the crowd thanking them. 

Harry tried his best to get her attention. Maybe she had seen him, but just ignored him? He needed to talk to her. They had gone around the back and Harry lost sigh of his girl. “Sir where are they going exactly?” Harry asked a guard who stood near his seat. 

“They will be heading back towards the carpet, to leave for the reception I assume.” Harry nodded thanking the nice man. He carefully made his way down the aisle, pushing through the doors that lead to the entrance. He caught a glimpse of her. The dress being a big help in spotting her. “Y/N! Please wait,” harry shouted. 

She froze and looked over her shoulder. Y/N hesitated still looking at him before  deciding to make her way towards him. her arms locked behind her back and she stood directly in front of him. “Harry you made it.” He bit his lip looking into her beautiful big eyes. 

“Would not miss it for the world.” Thunder cracked above them. Both instinctively looking up tot he sky. “I’m sorry,” the two spoke at the same time, laughing right after. “I’m really sorry for all I said Harry,” Y/N looked down at her feet. He reached out and tilted her chin up to him. 

His thumb ran over her soft skin. “No baby, I’m the one who should be sorry. You are alway there for me. Cheering me on. I need to be doing the same.” She melted at Harry’s words. He always knew how to do that for her. She would be lying if she said she wasn’t happy he was here. Y/N secretly hoped that he would show. 

Her lips parted to speak but Harry pulled her into his arms wrapping his arms around her waist. His nose nuzzling into her neck that smelled of a daisy perfume. “Harry?”


“Don’t let me go.”
